27 Jul 2015 04:44






A number of people have noted that vacuums shouldn't have an internal temperature. This was initially an intentional discrepancy that I thought made the anomaly a little stranger. However, upon reviewing the article, I can see that it isn't a sufficiently developed aspect of the object, and only serves to distract the reader from the rest of the article. As such, I've changed the term  to something a bit more appropriate. Thanks for the feedback.





